+# Agent Context: Adapting `cpa-sim` in `cpa-testbench`
+
+This context file is for agents implementing or extending `cpa-testbench` to execute realistic CPA lab design studies against `cpa-sim`.
+
+## Goal
+Use `cpa-sim` as the simulation backend and keep testbench experiments configuration-first so lab teams can iterate without editing Python source.
+
+## Expected integration shape
+- `scripts/run_pipeline.py` (or a successor runner) should:
+  1. Load one experiment YAML.
+  2. Resolve lab component presets from `configs/lab/components.yaml`.
+  3. Build a `cpa-sim` pipeline stage list.
+  4. Run simulation.
+  5. Return structured metrics for optimization + plotting.
+
+## Canonical config layering
+Use this layering for reproducible runs:
+1. `configs/lab/components.yaml` (site-specific hardware presets).
+2. `configs/lab/optimization.yaml` (search space + metric composition).
+3. `configs/lab/experiment_matrix.yaml` (candidate design sweeps).
+4. Optional CLI overrides (`--set key=value`).
+
+## Lab-specific component mapping
+### Fibers
+Represent as named presets with all parameters required by `cpa-sim` fiber stages:
+- length
+- dispersion terms
+- nonlinearity
+- attenuation
+
+### EDFAs
+Represent fixed hardware + tunables separately:
+- fixed: model/vendor, ASE model choice
+- tunable: gain target, pump current, saturation powers
+
+### Lasers
+Capture:
+- center wavelength
+- spectral width / pulse duration
+- repetition rate
+- energy or power constraints
+
+### Gratings (compressor/stretcher)
+Capture geometry:
+- lines per mm
+- incidence angle
+- separation / path length
+- diffraction order assumptions
+
+## Suggested stage naming conventions
+Use deterministic stage IDs to make optimization logs and plots interpretable:
+- `laser_seed`
+- `fiber_stretcher`
+- `edfa_preamp`
+- `fiber_booster`
+- `grating_compressor`
+
+## Metrics expected from each run
+At minimum emit:
+- compressed pulse duration (fs)
+- spectral bandwidth (nm)
+- peak power (kW)
+- nonlinear phase (`B_integral`)
+- efficiency / transmission
+
+Keep these under a stable dict so optimization code can combine metrics safely.
+
+## Compatibility notes
+- Keep adapter code isolated under `src/cpa_testbench/` (for example `adapters/cpa_sim_adapter.py`).
+- Avoid lab-specific constants in runner code; use config keys only.
+- Preserve deterministic seeds for any stochastic substep.
