+# Agent Context: Graphs for lab-meeting tradeoff reviews
+
+Use this playbook when generating visual outputs from `cpa-testbench` runs.
+
+## Required graph set
+1. **Pareto scatter**
+   - X: pulse duration (fs)
+   - Y: peak power (kW)
+   - Color: B-integral
+   - Marker: candidate family / architecture
+
+2. **Parallel coordinates**
+   - Axes: key design params + core metrics
+   - Highlight top-N candidates by composite score
+
+3. **Sensitivity tornado/bar chart**
+   - Show relative score impact for each tunable parameter.
+
+4. **Constraint heatmap**
+   - Pairwise grid for two high-impact parameters with feasible/infeasible regions.
+
+## Presentation-ready conventions
+- Always annotate 3â€“5 recommended candidates.
+- Include units in all labels.
+- Use consistent color map across runs.
+- Export both PNG (slides) and SVG (publication-quality edits).
+
+## Minimal artifact list per run
+- `artifacts/<run_id>/trials.csv`
+- `artifacts/<run_id>/summary.json`
+- `artifacts/<run_id>/plots/pareto.png`
+- `artifacts/<run_id>/plots/parallel_coords.png`
+- `artifacts/<run_id>/plots/sensitivity.png`
+- `artifacts/<run_id>/plots/constraint_heatmap.png`
+
+## Suggested plotting backend
+Prefer `phys_sims_utils.harness.plotting` helpers first.
+If custom plots are needed, use matplotlib/seaborn but keep data extraction in one reusable utility.
