+# Agent Context: Using `phys-sims-utils` for ML optimization
+
+This file defines how agents should connect `cpa-testbench` outputs to `phys-sims-utils` optimization and reporting utilities.
+
+## Goal
+Support both single-metric and multi-metric optimization of `cpa-sim` designs using `phys-sims-utils.ml` and `phys-sims-utils.harness`.
+
+## Required optimization capabilities
+1. Optimize one metric (example: minimize pulse duration).
+2. Optimize weighted combinations (example: duration + B-integral + efficiency penalty).
+3. Produce Pareto-style tradeoff artifacts for lab design review.
+
+## Preferred strategy stack
+Start with a robust default sequence:
+1. Sobol/random exploration to map feasible region.
+2. CMA-ES local refinement on promising regions.
+3. Optional restarts with modified weights.
+
+## Param-space contract
+Parameter names should be human-readable and map to config fields, e.g.:
+- `fiber_stretcher.length_m`
+- `edfa_preamp.gain_db`
+- `grating_compressor.separation_m`
+
+Use bounded spaces only; avoid unbounded optimization params.
+
+## Metric composition contract
+Define objective functions explicitly in config.
+
+Example scalar objective:
+`score = w1 * norm(duration_fs) + w2 * norm(B_integral) - w3 * norm(peak_power_kw)`
+
+Also record raw metrics for each trial so post-hoc reweighting is possible without rerunning simulations.
+
+## Trial artifact schema expectations
+Each trial should persist:
+- parameters
+- scalar score
+- raw metric dict
+- constraints/pass-fail flags
+- seed and run metadata
+
+## Fallback behavior
+If optimization packages are missing:
+- fall back to deterministic sweep mode,
+- still generate comparable CSV/JSON outputs,
+- log a warning with install guidance.
